<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-18T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-18T12:00:00-05:00" n="961" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d961">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Italy)/8–1345:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-18T13:00:00-04:00">August 18,
                                    1945—1 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1376. Urtel 2321 [<hi rend="italic">2329</hi>], Aug 13. Dept would have
                            no objection to return of Bolzano Province to Ital administration if in
                            opinion of SAC and AC there is no reason for retention of AMG. Ital Govt
                            should be informed, however, that return is without prejudice to final
                            disposition of Bolzano territory.</p>
                        <p>It is presumed SAC will recommend to CCS modification of Fan 536<note n="20" xml:id="d961fn1">See footnote 7, <ref target="#pg_1012">p.
                                    1012</ref>.</note> before proceeding with this matter.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>